<H2>RNA Structure and Sequence alignment</H2>

<B><font color=#AA7700>NEW:</font></B> Foldalign version 2.1.1
   is now available.
   Get the software <A HREF="software/index.html">here</A>.<BR>
<B><font color=#AA7700>NEW:</font></B> FoldalignM version 1.0.1
   is now available.
   Get the software <A HREF="software/index.html">here</A>.<BR>
The FOLDALIGN web server 2.1.0.A is available 
<A HREF="server/index.html">here</A>.<BR>
<P>
The new Semi-Automated RNA Sequence Editor <A
HREF="http://sarse.ku.dk/">SARSE</A> might also be of interest.
<p>

<P><BR>
FOLDALIGN an algorithm for local or global simultaneous folding and aligning
two or more RNA sequences and is based on the Sankoffs algorithm (SIAM J. Appl.
Math., 45:810-825, 1985). Foldalign can make pairwise local or global
alignments and structure predictions. FoldalignM makes a multiple global
alignment and structure prediction.

<!-- 
The early implementation is constrained to stemloop type
structure only, see <A HREF="http://www.bioinf.au.dk/foldalign">old foldalign
server (1.0)</A> or the <A HREF="http://www.bioinf.au.dk/slash">slash
server</A> for details. 
-->

<P><BR>
<H3>Recent references</H3>

<!-- REFERENCE BEGIN -->
<I><A HREF="http://compbiol.plosjournals.org/perlserv/?request=get-document&doi=10.1371/journal.pcbi.0030193&ct=1">
Fast Pairwise Structural RNA Alignments by Pruning of the Dynamical Programming
Matrix</A></I>,<BR>
Havgaard JH, Torarinsson E, Gorodkin J. PLOS computational biology. 3:e193, 2007
<P>

<I><A HREF="http://bioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/23/8/926">
Multiple structural alignment and clustering of RNA sequences</A></I>,<BR>
Torarinsson E, Havgaard JH, Gorodkin J. Bioinformatics. 23:926-32, 2007.
<P>

<I><A HREF="http://nar.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/33/suppl_2/W650">
The FOLDALIGN web server for pairwise structural RNA alignment and mutual motif
search</A></I>,<br>
J. H. Havgaard, R. B. Lyngsø, and J. Gorodkin. Nucleic Acids Research
33:W650-W653, 2005. 

